race.comment: SHE'S CAPITANA (8) got the job done last start in a 1000m maiden at Northam, winning by 0.9L and turning in a strong figure to do so. She jumped favourite there but showed plenty of class and this looks to shape nicely for her again with Pike sticking. Looks a nice filly on the rise and can notch up back-to-back wins. LAST STYLEBENDER (1) led off a 72-day break at Ascot over 1000m and was only collared late, beaten 0.2L by a progressive type. Fitter for that effort and should be prominent in the run once again. Easier here and will give them something to chase. OVERDRIVE (3) was well backed first-up but couldn't fend off her rivals late, beaten 1.5L after sitting on the speed. Better for that run and Parnham sticks in this similar race. Fitter now and can go a couple better. PAINT IT RED (6) will find this much easier than her recent efforts and her best form would see her hard to beat. KING'S DRAMA (2) is racing well and has to be included.
